Everbright Securities Company Limited is one of the largest securities brokerage by assets in China, controlled by state-owned financial conglomerate, China Everbright Group. It was founded in 1996 and is based in Shanghai.
It was listed on the Shanghai Stock Exchange in 2009 with capital raising of CNÂ¥10.96 billion. It was the second IPO by a Chinese brokerage, following CITIC Securities in 2002.
On 2 February 2015, Everbright Securities Co Ltd announced its agreement to buy Sun Hung Kai Financial's 70% stake for HK$4.1 billion.


